<subSubSection id="289C6535FFFC9074FF6AF875FAD97AAE" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="603936BEFFFC9074FF6AF875FAD97AAE" blockId="16.[151,1437,1664,2040]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFC9074FF6AF875F87D7A85" bold="true" box="[199,353,1977,2003]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFC9074FEC5F876FBAF7A82" baseAuthorityName="Delmastro" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[360,691,1978,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFC9074FEC5F876FBAF7A82" box="[360,691,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Oxynoemacheilus banarescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Devrekani and Yenice/Filiyos drainages in the Anatolian Black Sea basin. See 
<figureCitation id="F8BD2A3BFFFC9074FE50F812FB227AAE" box="[509,574,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1090]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Records of species of the O. bergianus group. Different colours indicate different molecular groups within species. Grey circles indicate records of O. simavicus without assignment to a molecular group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479756/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
for the distribution of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="289C6535FFFD9076FF6AFF5AF85B7C17" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="603936BEFFFD9075FF6AFF5AFB447C4B" blockId="17.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FF6AFF5AF8277DE6" bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FEE8FF5AFB8D7DE6" baseAuthorityName="Delmastro" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[325,657,150,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FEE8FF5AFB8D7DE6" box="[325,657,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Oxynoemacheilus banarescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FB2CFF5BFC097DE6" box="[1153,1301,150,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergianus">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FB2CFF5BFC097DE6" box="[1153,1301,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">O. bergianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by a minimum K2P distance of 2.9% to 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FD8EFF77FBA97D82" box="[547,693,186,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergianus">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FD8EFF77FBA97D82" box="[547,693,186,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">O. bergianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the DNA barcode region and it is supported by PTP, mPTP and ASAP. We were not able to find a reliable, consistent external character to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FBE2FF13FDF77DAE" baseAuthorityName="Delmastro" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[1103,1259,222,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FBE2FF13FDF77DAE" box="[1103,1259,222,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">O. banarescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from any of the other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FEDAFECFFB147C4A" box="[375,520,258,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergianus">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FEDAFECFFB147C4A" box="[375,520,258,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">O. bergianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<caption id="34F96636FFFD9075FF3AF907FDCE7A51" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479758" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6479758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479758/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" startId="17.[151,250,1739,1763]" targetBox="[151,1436,308,1715]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph id="603936BEFFFD9075FF3AF907FDCE7A51" blockId="17.[151,1437,1739,1799]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FF3AF907F80F7BB5" bold="true" box="[151,275,1739,1763]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FEB7F907FB9A7BB5" authority=", FSJF" authorityName="FSJF" box="[282,646,1739,1763]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FEB7F907FB597BB5" box="[282,581,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Oxynoemacheilus banarescui</emphasis>
, FSJF
</taxonomicName>
