</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="603936BEFFFD9076FF6AF8FAF85B7C17" blockId="17.[151,1437,1845,2016]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<bibRefCitation id="04174B4FFFFD9075FF6AF8FAF8BA7A06" author="Turan, D. &amp; Kaya, C. &amp; Kalayci, G. &amp; Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I." box="[199,422,1845,1872]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="458 - 468" refId="ref29942" refString="Turan, D., Kaya, C., Kalayci, G., Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I. (2019) Oxynoemacheilus cemali, a new species of stone loach (Teleostei: Nemacheilidae) from the Coruh River drainage. Journal of Fish Biology, 94 (3), 458 - 468. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13909" type="journal article" year="2019">
Turan 
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FEB9F8FAF84C7A19" box="[276,336,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
published two sequences (GenBank accession number: 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFD9075FB9BF8F9FDA77A19" box="[1078,1211,1845,1871]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH469261" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">MH469261</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFD9075FB64F8F9FC517A06" box="[1225,1357,1845,1872]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH469262" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">MH469262</accessionNumber>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FA2CF8FAF80E7A25" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FA2CF8FAF80E7A25" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">O. banarescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the stream Devrekani, closely clustering with our sequences from the same drainage. But 
<bibRefCitation id="04174B4FFFFD9075FAF7F896F83E7ACE" author="Turan, D. &amp; Kaya, C. &amp; Kalayci, G. &amp; Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I." pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="458 - 468" refId="ref29942" refString="Turan, D., Kaya, C., Kalayci, G., Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I. (2019) Oxynoemacheilus cemali, a new species of stone loach (Teleostei: Nemacheilidae) from the Coruh River drainage. Journal of Fish Biology, 94 (3), 458 - 468. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13909" type="journal article" year="2019">
Turan 
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FF3AF8B2F9D57AC1" box="[151,201,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
submitted three additional sequences (
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFD9075FD7AF8B1FA417ACE" box="[727,861,1917,1944]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018854" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">MH018854</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFD9075FCC4F8B1FAF17ACE" box="[873,1005,1917,1944]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018855" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">MH018855</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFD9075FC55F8B1FD607ACE" box="[1016,1148,1917,1944]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018856" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">MH018856</accessionNumber>
) to GenBank, which they omitted from the manuscript. Sungur (2020) downloaded all five sequences labelled as “ 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFD9075FBC0F86DF8277A89" authority=", Devrekani" authorityName="Devrekani" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFD9075FBC0F86DF9A57A89" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Oxynoemacheilus banarescui</emphasis>
, Devrekani
</taxonomicName>
stream: Kızılırmak Basin” from GenBank. The Devrekani does not flow to the Kızılırmak.As Cüneyt Kaya is a co-author of the study of 
<bibRefCitation id="04174B4FFFFE9076FDB0FF5BFBF27DE7" author="Turan, D. &amp; Kaya, C. &amp; Kalayci, G. &amp; Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I." box="[541,750,151,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" pagination="458 - 468" refId="ref29942" refString="Turan, D., Kaya, C., Kalayci, G., Baycelebi, E. &amp; Aksu, I. (2019) Oxynoemacheilus cemali, a new species of stone loach (Teleostei: Nemacheilidae) from the Coruh River drainage. Journal of Fish Biology, 94 (3), 458 - 468. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13909" type="journal article" year="2019">
Turan 
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFE9076FDCBFF5BFB817DE7" box="[614,669,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
and the present study, it is now possible to clarify the reasons for this omission. Indeed, the sequences 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFE9076FDF0FF76FBFD7D83" box="[605,737,186,213]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018854" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">MH018854</accessionNumber>
, 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFE9076FD41FF76FA6C7D83" box="[748,880,186,213]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018855" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">MH018855</accessionNumber>
, and 
<accessionNumber id="7FD5AB5DFFFE9076FC06FF76FD307D83" box="[939,1068,186,213]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH018856" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">MH018856</accessionNumber>
do not originate from fishes collected in the Kızılırmak or Devrekani drainages, but in the Büyük Melen (
<geoCoordinate id="05B25079FFFE9076FC6AFF12FD247DAF" box="[967,1080,222,249]" degrees="40.8358" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" precision="5" value="40.8358">40.8358N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="05B25079FFFE9076FB93FF13FDB77DAF" box="[1086,1195,223,249]" degrees="31.1100" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" precision="5" value="31.11">31.1100E</geoCoordinate>
) and it is therefore no surprise that they do not cluster with 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFE9076FD94FECFFBCB7C4B" box="[569,727,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="banarescui">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFE9076FD94FECFFBCB7C4B" box="[569,727,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">O. banarescui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with 
<taxonomicName id="A7864D3DFFFE9076FCEFFECFFACF7C4A" box="[834,979,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Oxynoemacheilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simavicus">
<emphasis id="52F2EAACFFFE9076FCEFFECFFACF7C4A" box="[834,979,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">O. simavicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Büyük Melen in our molecular dataset (
<figureCitation id="F8BD2A3BFFFE9076FF59FEEBF82A7C17" box="[244,310,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1767,1791]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,456,1734]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[151,1436,453,1744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood estimation of the phylogenetic relationships based on the mitochondrial COI barcode region (GTR model, discrete Gamma distribution for rate differences with 5 categories +G parameter = 0.1781). Nucleotide positions with less than 98% site coverage were eliminated, resulting in 581 analysed positions. Numbers of major nodes indicate bootstrap values above 80 from 1000 pseudoreplicates from the ML, MP and NJ method. Solid black bars right to the specimen labels indicate species demarcation results from PTP followed by the results of the mPTP approach as dashed bars and theASAP partitions in grey. Note that the dashed bar left extends to the right side including O. parvinae. The tree is drawn to scale (except to the outgroup) with branch lengths depicting number of substitutions per site." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479754/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
